                                                {% heroicon "outline", "code" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Kotlin</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            fritz2 heavily uses Kotlin standard features (especially flows) and has no external dependencies.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="pt-6">
                                <div class="flow-root bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-6 pb-8">
                                    <div class="-mt-6">
                                        <div>
                                          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-cyan-600 rounded-md shadow-lg">
                                            <span class="h-6 w-6 text-white">
                                                {% heroicon "outline", "switch-horizontal" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Data-Binding</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            fritz2 offers precise data-binding for your ui-elements. When your data changes, those - and only those - DOM-elements are updated,
                                            that are bound to parts of the model, that really have changed - no virtual dom needed.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="pt-6">
                                <div class="flow-root bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-6 pb-8">
                                    <div class="-mt-6">
                                        <div>
                                          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-cyan-600 rounded-md shadow-lg">
                                            <span class="h-6 w-6 text-white">
                                                {% heroicon "outline", "academic-cap" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Learn</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            fritz2 built around just a few basic concepts (Stores, Handlers, Tags, etc.).
                                            You can easily learn how to use them from our documentation or the examples we provide. Enjoy!
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="pt-6">
                                <div class="flow-root bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-6 pb-8">
                                    <div class="-mt-6">
                                        <div>
                                          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-cyan-600 rounded-md shadow-lg">
                                            <span class="h-6 w-6 text-white">
                                                {% heroicon "outline", "trending-up" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Scale</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            fritz2 allows you to build small apps very fast with a few lines of code as well as enterprise
                                            scale applications with a focus on reusable components, clean code and structure.
                                            The functional reactive concept makes the resulting code easy to read and to maintain.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="pt-6">
                                <div class="flow-root bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-6 pb-8">
                                    <div class="-mt-6">
                                        <div>
                                          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-cyan-600 rounded-md shadow-lg">
                                            <span class="h-6 w-6 text-white">
                                                {% heroicon "outline", "library" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Complete</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            fritz2 includes everything you need to start your project:
                                            state management (even for complex nested models), validation, routing, REST, WebSockets, WebComponents
                                            as well as a set of tailor-made headless components.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="pt-6">
                                <div class="flow-root bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-6 pb-8">
                                    <div class="-mt-6">
                                        <div>
                                          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-cyan-600 rounded-md shadow-lg">
                                            <span class="h-6 w-6 text-white">
                                                {% heroicon "outline", "puzzle" %}
                                            </span>
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <h3 class="mt-8 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Reuse</h3>
                                        <p class="mt-5 text-base text-gray-500">
                                            using Koltin's multiplatform-abilities, you have to write your data classes and validation code (!)
                                            just once and use it in your client and server.
                                            Use a tool-chain (Gradle, IDEA, etc.) you know well to jump right in and build your apps.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

